This paper deals with improving language models, which is a core topic in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed method involves using a curriculum learning approach to gradually change the policy of the model, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method also involves sampling from a nearest-neighbor distribution, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, these five categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
